html: Senator Fischer has pocketed more than $1.3 million from corporate political action committees (PACs) in her career, and more than $1 million for her re-election campaign.
text: Senator Fischer has pocketed more than $1.3 million from corporate political action committees (PACs) in her career, and more than $1 million for her re-election campaign.

html: Fischer took nearly $134,000 from telecommunications and cable company PACs, including Comcast, Verizon and Time Warner. She also voted to overturn an FCC privacy rule and allow internet service providers to sell customer data — including Nebraskans’ internet browsing history.
text: Fischer took nearly $134,000 from telecommunications and cable company PACs, including Comcast, Verizon and Time Warner. She also voted to overturn an FCC privacy rule and allow internet service providers to sell customer data — including Nebraskans’ internet browsing history.

html: Fischer has long-supported the pipeline project by the Canadian oil giant, which is accused of trampling the rights of Nebraska landowners.

html: Fischer gladly accepted more than $93k from huge oil and gas interests, including TransCanada, which wants to build the controversial Keystone XL pipeline across Nebraska’s ecologically fragile Ogallala Aquifer.
